<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-11T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-11T22:36:00-05:00" n="1302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1302">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3566.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-11T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am informed through respectable sources that a signed organization of
                            10,000 men exists in the State of Vera Cruz to act in cooperation with
                            the rebels in the north, and that as soon as the American railway
                            servants go out they expect to begin destroying bridges and killing
                            Mexican railway employees on the Interoceanic and Mexican railways.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>